article.description: Hartford holds on to beat UMBC 55-52
article.headline: Hartford holds on to beat UMBC 55-52
article.linkText: Hartford holds on to beat UMBC 55-52
article.story: HARTFORD, Conn. -- Wes Cole scored 13 points and Corban Wroe added 11 as Hartford held on to beat Maryland-Baltimore County 55-52 on Tuesday night. Justin Graham chipped in 10 for Hartford (13-13, 6-7 American East Conference). Hartford led most of the second half but could never pull away from the Retrievers until Wroe drove for a layup to start a 7-1 run to go up 42-34 with 7:14 left. UMBC did not fold as Devarick Houston made two free throws to close to 54-52 with 11 seconds left. The Retrievers (3-23, 1-23), who have lost 14 of their last 15 games, limited Hartford to 21-of-56 shooting from the floor but hit only 14 of 46 field goal attempts themselves. Cody Joyce made 9 of 12 free throw attempts and had 17 points with nine rebounds for UMBC.
